{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"00ca3df6-faff-40de-8002-1e05efe04377","content":"Run **`dotnet workload update`**.\n\n- **`dotnet workload update`** – downloads and installs the latest versions of all installed workloads, aligning them with your current SDK. This is what you need after an SDK update.\n- **`dotnet workload repair`** – reinstalls the *same* versions already recorded; it fixes corrupted or missing files but won't pull newer packages.\n\nAfter updating:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\ndotnet build\n```\n\nIf the build still fails, check that you have the `maui` workload installed:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload list\n```\n\nIf it's missing, install it explicitly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload install maui\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"08440259-13e3-48a4-bc81-94f8a843b7eb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the difference between `dotnet workload update` and `dotnet workload repair` to fix a .NET MAUI build issue after an SDK update. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to look at any files.","outputTokens":235,"requestId":"A843:6D183:620D65:71B92C:69FBE208"},"id":"3474688d-f3e0-49f8-970e-ab9f8a1bcef9","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:51:27.071Z","parentId":"4f816896-f956-4303-91a5-5d45ed31e23e"}
